In [19]:
#@title
def dir_img(path):
  for item in sorted(os.listdir(path)):
    if ((item.endswith(".jpg"))or (item.endswith(".png"))or (item.endswith(".jpeg"))or (item.endswith(".gif"))):
      x_train.append(item)
      
    else:
      modified_path = path+"/"+item
      dir_img(modified_path)
  return x_train

def remove_usernames_links(tweet):
   tweet = re.sub('@[^\s]+','',tweet)
   tweet = re.sub('http[^\s]+','',tweet)
   return tweet

from nltk.corpus import stopwords
from nltk.tokenize import word_tokenize
stop_words = set(stopwords.words('english'))
", ".join(stopwords.words('english'))
def remove_stopwords(text):
    return " ".join([word for word in text.split() if word not in stop_words])

# creating embedded dictionary to store embeddings
embedding_index = {}
with open('/content/glove.twitter.27B.200d.txt', encoding='utf-8') as f:
    for line in f:
        values = line.split()
        word = values[0]
        coefs = np.asarray(values[1:], dtype='float32')
        embedding_index[word] = coefs

In [51]:
# create embedding matrix
embedding_matrix = np.zeros((vocab_size+1, 200))
for word, i in word_index.items():
    embedding_vector = embedding_index.get(word)
    if embedding_vector is not None:
        embedding_matrix[i] = embedding_vector

In [54]:
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Input
from tensorflow.keras.models import Model
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Dense
from tensorflow.keras.layers import LSTM
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Embedding
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Flatten
In [55]:
deep_inputs = Input(shape=(len_of_seq,))
embedding = Embedding(vocab_size+1, 200,   input_length=len_of_seq)(deep_inputs)
embedding = Flatten()(embedding)
embed_out = Dense(1, activation='linear')(embedding)
deep_model = Model(inputs=deep_inputs, outputs=embed_out)
deep_model.compile(loss='categorical_crossentropy',
              optimizer='adam',
               metrics=['accuracy'])

import glob
image_paths=[]
def dir_img(path):  
  for item in sorted(os.listdir(path)):
    if ((item.endswith(".jpg"))or (item.endswith(".png"))or (item.endswith(".jpeg"))or (item.endswith(".gif"))):
      x_train.append(item)      
      
      
    else:
      modified_path = path+"/"+item
      dir_img(modified_path)
  return x_train
In [116]:

image_paths = []

import cv2
import numpy as np

# Load the images from the paths
images = []
for path in x_train_final:
    image = cv2.imread(path)  # Read the image from the path
    image = cv2.cvtColor(image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)  # Convert BGR to RGB format
    image = cv2.resize(image, (224, 224))  # Resize image to (224, 224)
    images.append(image)

# Convert the list of images to a numpy array
x_train_images = np.array(images)

embedding_index = {}
with open('/content/glove.twitter.27B.200d.txt', encoding='utf-8') as f:
    for line in f:
        values = line.split()
        word = values[0]
        coefs = np.asarray(values[1:], dtype='float32')
        embedding_index[word] = coefs

deep_inputs = Input(shape=(len_of_seq,))
embedding = Embedding(vocab_size+1, 200,   input_length=len_of_seq)(deep_inputs)
flat_embed = Flatten()(embedding)
text_1 = Dense(50, activation='relu')(embedding)
text_2 = Dense(25, activation='relu')(embedding)
flat_text = Flatten()(text_2)
In [253]:
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Conv2D
from tensorflow.keras.layers import MaxPooling2D

image_inputs = Input(shape=(224, 224, 3))
conv11 = Conv2D(128, kernel_size=4, activation='relu')(image_inputs)
pool11 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(conv11)
conv12 = Conv2D(64, kernel_size=4, activation='relu')(pool11)
pool12 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(conv12)
flat_image = Flatten()(pool12)
In [256]:
from keras.backend import concatenate
merge_model=concatenate([flat_text,flat_image])
In [257]:
hidden_1 = Dense(50, activation='relu')(merge_model)
hidden_2 = Dense(25, activation='relu')(hidden_1)
output_final = Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')(hidden_2)
final_model=Model(inputs=[deep_inputs,image_inputs],outputs=output_final)

final_model.compile(loss='binary_crossentropy', optimizer='adam', metrics=['accuracy'])
